'''KAON''' ('''Karlsruhe ontology''') is an [[Ontology engineering|ontology]] infrastructure developed by the [[University of Karlsruhe]] and the [[Forschungszentrum Informatik|Research Center for Information Technologies]] in [[Karlsruhe]].
Its first incarnation was developed in 2002 and supported an enhanced version of [[Resource Description Framework|RDF]] ontologies.
Several tools like the graphical ontology editor OIModeler or the KAON Server were based on KAON.

There are [[ontology learning]] companion tools which take non-annotated natural language text as input: TextToOnto (KAON-based) and Text2Onto (KAON2-based). Text2Onto is based on the Probabilistic Ontology Model (POM).<ref>{{cite web|author=Philipp Cimiano, Johanna Völker|title=Text2Onto: A Framework for Ontology Learning and Data-driven Change Discovery|url=http://people.aifb.kit.edu/jvo/publications/Text2Onto_nldb_2005.pdf|location=[[University of Karlsruhe]]|publisher=Institute of Applied Informatics and Formal Description Methods (AIFB)|year=2005|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719222645/http://people.aifb.kit.edu/jvo/publications/Text2Onto_nldb_2005.pdf|archivedate=2011-07-19|df=}}</ref>

In 2005, the first version of KAON2 was released, offering fast reasoning support for [[Web Ontology Language|OWL]] ontologies. KAON2 is not backward-compatible with KAON. KAON2 is developed as a joint effort of the Information Process Engineering (IPE) at the [[Forschungszentrum Informatik|Research Center for Information Technologies]] (FZI), the Institute of Applied Informatics and Formal Description Methods (AIFB) at the [[University of Karlsruhe]], and the Information Management Group (IMG) at the [[University of Manchester]].<ref>{{cite web|title=KAON2: Ontology Management for the Semantic Web|url=http://kaon2.semanticweb.org/|publisher=[[Semantic Web|semanticweb.org]]}}</ref>

KAON, TextToOnto, and Text2Onto are open source, based on [[Java (programming language)|Java]]. KAON2 is not open source,<ref>{{cite web|title=KAON2: Ontology Management for the Semantic Web, Download|url=http://kaon2.semanticweb.org/#download|publisher=[[Semantic Web|semanticweb.org]]}}</ref> but the executable can be downloaded from the KAON2 site.

